display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathrm {R}\Gamma (K_A),\mathrm {R}\Gamma ((K_\mathbb {C},F)),\mathrm {R}\Gamma (\alpha ))]]></fr:tex> is a Hodge complex of weight <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p><fr:p>When <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A=\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex>, we simply speak of Hodge complexes and cohomological Hodge complexes.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:p>The following statement reformulates a part of classical Hodge theory (cf. <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.2.1"
href="hodge-theory-ii-2.2.1.xml"
number="2.2.1" />).</fr:p><fr:tree
