xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1339</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.1.3</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.1.3.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Scholium</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>8.1.3</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-8.1</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a complex K√§hler variety.
    Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K_\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> be the complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Z}[0]]]></fr:tex> consisting of the constant sheaf <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> in degree <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K_\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> be the holomorphic de Rham complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Omega _X^\bullet ]]></fr:tex>, with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> its stupid filtration.
    We have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \colon  K_\mathbb {Z}\otimes \mathbb {C}\simeq \mathbb {C}[0]\xrightarrow {\approx }\Omega _X^\bullet ]]></fr:tex> (the Poincar√© lemma), and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_\mathbb {Z},(K_\mathbb {C},F),\alpha )]]></fr:tex> is a cohomological Hodge complex of weight <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
