display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-complex</fr:em> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> consists of:

    
 <html:ol
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(ùõº) &quot;">
        a complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K_A\in \operatorname {Ob}\mathrm {D}^+(A)]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^k(K_A)]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-module of finite type for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k]]></fr:tex>;
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(ùõΩ) &quot;">
        a filtered complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}},W)\in \operatorname {Ob}\mathrm {D}^+F(A\otimes \mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex> (for an <fr:em>increasing</fr:em> filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex>) and an isomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}\simeq  K_A\otimes \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {D}^+(A\otimes \mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex>;
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(ùõæ) &quot;">
        a bifiltered complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_\mathbb {C},W,F)\in \operatorname {Ob}\mathrm {D}^+F_w(\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex> (for an <fr:em>increasing</fr:em> filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex> and a <fr:em>decreasing</fr:em> filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>) and an isomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \colon (K_\mathbb {C},W)\simeq (K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}},W)\otimes \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {D}^+F(\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p><fr:p>The following axiom must be satisfied:

    <fr:tree
